Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA  JOHANNESBURG - Standard Bank intends to re-hire workers fired for refusing to comply with its mandatory Covid-19 vaccination policy. The bank withdrew its vaccination policy on Monday after banking union Sasbo was set to challenge it. READ: COVID-19 | Standard Bank scraps mandatory vaccination policy At least 40 of the union's members were fired by the bank for non-compliance. Standard Bank SA CEO Lungisa Fuzile says following the withdrawal of the policy, the bank was engaging in re-employment opportunities. 